quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
63,5,"When it is said to them: “Come, Allah's Messenger will seek forgiveness for you,” they (contemptuously) shake their heads and you see them holding back in pride. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
63,6,"It is all the same for them whether you ask forgiveness for them or not; for Allah shall never forgive them. {1} Surely Allah does not direct the transgressing folk to the Right Way. {2}",footnotes:1:Two things have been stated in this verse. First
63,7,"It is they who say: “Give nothing to those who are with the Messenger of Allah so that they may disperse.” (They say so although) the treasures of the heavens and the earth belong to Allah. But the hypocrites do not understand."
63,8,"They say: “When we return to Madinah, the honourable ones will drive out from it those that are abject.” {1} In truth, all honour belongs to Allah, and to His Messenger, and to the believers. {2} But the hypocrites do not know.",footnotes:1:Zaid bin Arqam says: When I reported these words of Abdullah bin Ubayy to the Prophet (peace be upon him)
63,9,"Believers, {1} let your possessions and your offspring not make you negligent of Allah's remembrance. {2} For whoso does that, they will be the losers.",footnotes:1:Now a word of admonition is being addressed to all those people who have entered Islam
63,10,"And spend of what Allah has granted you by way of sustenance before death should come to any of you and he should say: “Lord, why did You not defer my return for a while so that I might give alms and be among the righteous?”"
63,11,"But when a person's term comes to an end, Allah never grants any respite. Allah is well aware of all that you do."
